4. PO No. B60-044/GSA PO No. 4FU-660/ICA PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00335
Tank Fabric 2 each (broken cases)
Shipped on S.S. La Salle, B/L No. 2. Date of arrival Keelung: Jan. 19, 1962.
B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on Jan. 26, 1962.
To date we understand that BES have not informed CUSA/2D that the property is in their yard.

5. PO No. 60.282 /GS/. PO No. 1FU-148/ICA PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00334
Refrigerators 20 units
Shipped on S.S. Pres. Garfield, B/L No. 2.
Date of arrival Keelung: Nov. 30, 1961.
B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on December 6, 1961. On Jan. 15, 1962 BES advised CUSA/2D these items in their yard. On Jan. 25, 1962 CUSA/2D instructed the recipient to take delivery from the BES yard.
These refrigerators were procured for Kachsiung V-I School and Taipei Institute of Technology recommended by BD in Mr. Murray's memo dated Jan. 26, 1961.
These items are stored along the road cutside of the BES yard.
